    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="“听蝼蛄叫还不种庄稼了？”"><a href="#“听蝼蛄叫还不种庄稼了？”" class="headerlink" title="“听蝼蛄叫还不种庄稼了？”"></a>“听蝼蛄叫还不种庄稼了？”</h1><p>tags：碎碎念</p><hr><blockquote><p><em>There were many mole crickets and we could hear them chirp at night. There was a popular expression among us: “Don’t stop planting wheat just because mole crickets chirp,” which means you should not let little problems or risks prevent you from doing what is necessary. I still follow such wisdom today.</em>  Weijian Shan <em>Out of the Gobi</em></p></blockquote><p><img src="https://s1.ax1x.com/2020/07/06/UPJU4P.jpg" alt="UPJU4P.jpg"></p><p>去年初秋翻到这一段时心中忽有所悟，暗下决心要完成一桩拖了很久的事情，到本月初终于告成。聊记一笔。</p>]]></content>
    
